title: The Spin | Off the scent: how Atherton and Katich thrived in cricket without all senses intact
description: The seasonâ€™s onset brings a host of evocative smells, which two esteemed players have never been able to savourOn the weekend, a friend and I went walking. As we strolled along the River Goyt, a sweet smell hit us like a packet of Love Hearts, which, as it turns out, is pretty much what it was. We had inadvertently walked past the Swizzels factory â€“ producer of Parma Violets, Rainbow Drops and more in the Sett Valley since the company moved out of blitzed London in 1940, to an old textile mill in New Mills, Derbyshire.Alongside the sugary cloud drifted a junk shop of memories, sweets handed out at jelly and ice-cream parties, shared on the curb outside the corner shop, sucked on the way home from school. Later on, we passed a man pushing a mower to and fro on his front lawn and that fresh hit set off a whole other chain of flashbacks. As a cricket lover, you probably know where this is going. title: Can India's men dominate white ball cricket for a decade?
description: On this week's Stumped, Alison Mitchell, Brett Sprigg and Charu Sharmu discuss Indiaâ€™s dominance of the menâ€™s white ball game - will it continue all the way through to next yearâ€™s T20 World Cup and beyond?
